---
title: Deconstructed Ratatouille with Balsamic Tomatoes and Feta and Garlicky Ciabatta
description: The definition of deconstructed is ‘to reduce something to its constitutent parts’. We’re not sure we agree completely with this - we wouldn’t say there is any reduction going on here. This dish is such a show stopper, that we wanted to let everything from the ratatouille and feta to the garlicky ciabatta absolutely shine!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/deconstructed-ratatouille-with-balsamic-tomatoes-6c5af5f0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/deconstructed-ratatouille-with-balsamic-tomatoes-92dfa577.pdf
cuisine: French
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
