source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/deconstructed-ratatouille-with-balsamic-tomates-26-5756ae5efd2cb9d1068b4567
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop each half into four pieces. Separate the onion layers. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and chop into slices 1cm wide. Cut the top off the @aubergine{1}, slice it lengthways into strips about 1cm wide, then chop the strips in half.

Put your onion, pepper and half the @cherry tomatoes{1} on a #baking tray{} with a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Sprinkle over the @dried Italian herbs{1.5%tsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and pop in your oven to cook for ~{20%mins}.

Meanwhile, cut the @courgette{1} in half lengthways, then cut each half lengthways again into four strips. Chop the strips into batons about the length of your little finger.

Slice the remaining tomatoes in half through the equator. Roughly chop half the @basil{½%bunch}. Put your tomatoes in a #bowl{} with the @balsamic vinegar{1}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} and mix together. Leave to the side. Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half through the middle and leave to the side.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium high heat with @olive oil{4%tbsp} and cook your aubergine slices (they need to be in a single layer so do this in two batches and add more oil when you add the next batch of aubergines if you need to). Sprinkle over a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and fry for ~{3-4%mins} on each side until charred and soft. Once cooked, remove the aubergine to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

There shouldn't be any oil left in the pan but if there is just wipe it out with some #kitchen paper{}. Season the courgettes with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Cook all in one layer without any olive oil (do this in two batches if you need to!); dry-fry on one side for ~{3-4%mins} until slightly charred, then turn the courgette batons over and cook on the other side for another ~{3-4%mins}. Remove the courgettes from the pan.

Once your onion, pepper and tomatoes are cooked, take them out of your oven. Crumble the @feta cheese{1} and add in your chopped basil. Stir everything together and cover with foil to keep warm. Turn your grill to high and place your ciabatta slices underneath. Grill them for ~{2-3%mins} on each side until they are nicely toasted, then remove.

Cut the @garlic clove{1} in half and rub the cut sides on each of your toasted ciabatta slices. Drizzle over @olive oil{2%tbsp}.

Put one ciabatta half on each plate, layer on your aubergine slices then pile on your veggie-feta mixture. Lay your courgettes on top and finish with your balsamic tomatoes and any leftover juices. Tear over your remaining basil and enjoy!